## 🛡️ What Must Be Done for Safe Production Deployment

### Priority 1: MUST DO (Before any users)

| # | Task | Impact |
|---|------|--------|
| 1 | **Connect frontend to real backend API** — Replace all mock data in [AuthContext](file:///c:/Users/jaikisan/Downloads/PairOn/app/src/context/AuthContext.tsx#4-10) and [MatchingContext](file:///c:/Users/jaikisan/Downloads/PairOn/app/src/context/MatchingContext.tsx#4-14) with actual HTTP/Socket.io calls | Core functionality |
| 2 | **Add Socket.io authentication** — Verify JWT on socket connection, reject unauthenticated sockets | Security |
| 3 | **Add rate limiting** — Use `express-rate-limit` on auth routes (5 attempts/min) and API routes (100 req/min) |Security |
| 4 | **Whitelist profile update fields** — Only allow `name`, `bio`, `skills`, `interests`, `experienceLevel` in PATCH `/profile` | Security |
| 5 | **Add admin role** — Add `role: 'user' \| 'admin'` to User model, protect admin routes with role check | Security |
| 6 | **Sanitize regex input** — Escape special characters in user search queries or use `$text` index | Security |
| 7 | **Add refresh token mechanism** — Short-lived access tokens (15min) + refresh tokens to prevent session hijacking | Security |
| 8 | **Environment validation** — Add startup check for required env vars (`JWT_SECRET`, `MONGODB_URI`) | Stability |

### Priority 2: SHOULD DO (Before scaling)

| # | Task | Impact |
|---|------|--------|
| 9 | **Implement credit spending endpoints** — POST `/api/credits/spend` with validation | Core feature |
| 10 | **Implement rating endpoints** — POST `/api/ratings` that updates user reputation average | Core feature |
| 11 | **Replace setInterval timer** — Use Redis pub/sub or client-side countdown with server validation at end | Scalability |
| 12 | **Add pagination** — All list endpoints should support `?page=1&limit=20` | Scalability |
| 13 | **Cap previousMatches array** — Use `$slice` to keep only last 100 matches | Performance |
| 14 | **Add proper error handling on frontend** — Toast notifications, retry logic, error boundaries | UX |
| 15 | **Add basic tests** — At minimum: auth routes, matching algorithm, credit transactions | Reliability |

### Priority 3: NICE TO HAVE (Post-launch)

| # | Task | Impact |
|---|------|--------|
| 16 | Move messages to a separate collection with cursor-based pagination | Performance |
| 17 | Add email verification on registration | Trust |
| 18 | Add OAuth (Google/GitHub) login | Growth |
| 19 | Add project showcase/gallery | Engagement |
| 20 | Build the admin dashboard with real data | Operations |

