## 📝 Summary

**The project has a strong vision and decent architecture, but it's essentially two separate apps right now — a mock frontend and a disconnected backend.** The #1 priority is wiring them together. After that, security hardening is critical before any real users touch the platform.

The credit and reputation systems are the core value proposition of your platform, and both are currently placeholder-only. Getting these working end-to-end should be your primary development focus.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Bottom line:** Don't build more features. Fix the foundation. Connect frontend ↔ backend → secure it → implement credits/reputation → then grow.
